              I always wondered why people didn't claim that they had wireless routers and it must have been somebody else using their connection.. <BR><BR>very hard to prove otherwise, i think. Most consumer grade routers don't keep logs unless you explicitly tell them to (at least, Linksys works this way) so you have a plausible excuse and they have no way to disprove it.<BR><BR><BR>Oh, and you don't tell them about the machine you use for your P2P... <img src="http://episteme.arstechnica.com/groupee_common/emoticons/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" width="15" height="15"><!--graemlin::p-->

              

              
              
